    "en": "Herbal preparation derived from Chinese rhubarb root. Made from the roots of the Chinese rhubarb plant, dahuang is a bitter, cooling herb for the meridians of the heart, spleen, stomach, liver and large intestine. It is traditionally used as a purgative ..."
